But lunch time they had literally EVERYTHING! First set 15 hours ,but no regrets #actor #background #movie #films #film #bg #crafty

This was my second time on a set in life. This one was the first that I booked through social media, even though this was just the 2nd one, I already felt like a pro. No managers, no agents, just me and a couple of selfies applying for everything, and actually GETTING gigs! 

I met some amazing people in this room, actors, photographers, chefs, etc. @dcyoungfly was coming in the room every 20-30 minutes to check on us, making sure we was good, which was wild to me since he was the star, bro crazy cool in person. Also the first time I saw the power of personality, @waytheofficial played this wild phone prank on us AND DC lmao this was a time where I thought the extras just needed to be quiet and fill spaces, but bro blew that mindset out the window for me, now, I show who I am on EVERY set bc of him and I'll always appreciate that. 

But, besides the production, one of the funniest moments of this day was when one of the other  extras went up talking to @lantbo asking about his "philisophical name" and turns out bruh thought that he was talking to EMMANUAL Hudson, not PHILLIP Hudson lol but he was still crazy chill about it, "gotta see it through, my boy" #actor #pettyclaimscourt #giglife #actorlife #setlife #background #movie #films #bg

I remember almost not applying for this one because it was "far away." But at the same time, all I could think was "hey, what else do I have to do, actors travel all the time." Luckily, I got booked for this gig, A/C went out that morning and I thought about just turning around, but I didn't want give out like that. 

This one ended up being a two-day set for me, first day, I sat in holding the whole day, 7a to 8p doing absolutely nothing. By the time they called us to set, the PA was coming out of location telling us that they didn't need us, but we're welcome to come back tomorrow and we "may be used." 

That point I figured it's free money to sit around so I'll come back. Fast forward to the next day, we were used from the jump! First thing in the morning it was "sign in, check with wardrobe and head to location after you eat!" 

After my DC set, I went in ready to be me! There were a lot of close ups of me that day, dancing, faces, etc. I don't know if they'll be used, but I don't care, I had a great time! I met @robingivens that day during production, a plethora of other big names, with @mariovanpeebles being among those names! In hindsight, I want to apologize to MVP for fanning out for a picture last minute, but my phone was on 2% and when would I ever get that opportunity again?! lol 

These days are long, but for BG, the stress is low and the times are good, I'm ready to see when this Christmas movie comes out, maybe I'll see myself #actor #acting #setlife #giglife #background #bg #film #movie #set

For this one, I can't say there was anything too glamorous about it. We met in a dirt lot, ate leftoer crafty, and sat in the heat for hours. However, I'd be remissed to say that the day wasn't worth it. Being able to meet @itstheolodge and chop it up about life and the business in itself made the day worth it. I was under the impression that I needed classes and headshots and all to get ahead, he let me know that if you have the look then you have the look, that's it. Your talent will take you where you need to, don't depend on accolades to show people who you are, and I carry that with me on every set. They selected me to be a stand-in on this set, and even though I wasn't used, I got to see my name on the call sheet. 

I shot with this show 3 days, so that's why my outfit changed, but nonetheless, that 2nd day/night was when the PA noticed me and wanted me to get in front of the camera more, even as a background guy, there were scenes that got reshot wanting me to do more crosswalk or engagement with the cast. 

I met with people that have been acting since I was born, I talked to ppl that dealt with Disney, with Marvel, with every streaming network you can pay for, and I learned from this gig that every set has a mood, every director has their ticks.But every opportunity, has its own separate opportunities...

This was my first (and only so far) overnight shoot. Call time was 7pm so I already knew it was going to be a long one. I gotta say, this particular set....was interesting to say the least. One thing I've learned throughout this process is to always look at the positives and the takaways from everything. Every venture will not be prize, but the experience/knowledge gained for future endeavors will be reward enough. This one was the first film/move set that I'd been on, and it was VERY different. Nonetheless, we got through it and I can't wait to see the finished product. #actor #actorlife #bg #background #setlife #set #gig #movie #films #film

Here was the day I learned those disclaimers when booking are real! At the bottom, where it says to charge all devices and bring something to keep yourself warm...yea hardheaded me. Got there and it was 46 degrees outside and not much warmer than that in the building, and guess who didn't bring a coat lol 

This was a 2 day shoot, day one I was literally just sitting around, they were doing the main character scenes and I  think I got used once and was just staying out of the way for the remainder. That second day though! First, I brought my coat (lol), and second, I was able to do MY thing! 

There was a certain scene that happened and I made a real life face instead of blending into the background, after that, they literally adjusted the scene to give me close up camera time to make that face again and bg banter when they said their lines! 

Now, there are good ways to ask for a picture and there are "not so good" ways. In the midst of resetting, a random came into location and told @officialtccarson "I know why I ain't recognize you, you done got old" to when I said "that ain't really the best way to ask for a pic fam" Actually got folks laughing and I was able to let TC know I'm also a member of THE Iota Phi Theta Fraternity, Inc. A legendary grip that I will always brag about now lol

Not to forget, but I met @blerdofmouth that day as well, an amazing stunt actor, weirdly, I kept staring at bro bc I thought he was Carlton from the Bel Air series lol. But this guy was great nonetheless (check em out) 

Extra special shoutout to @dejilaray as well! Great actor and great person overall. That wrap when you stopped me to ask me what my name was, I actually felt like I was doing something right, like more than an extra, and I'll always appreciate that. 

#actor #actorlife #gig #giglife #set #setlife #bg #background #film #movie #series

This had to be one of the most exciting scary days I've ever had! I met @coldplunge_bryan on my very FIRST set, but at lunch he mentioned his #coldplunge and gave me a lot of insight on the industry in a short amount of time. That's when I was invited to partake in the #coldplunge 

TBH I never looked into the health benefits or any of that from ice baths, mainly bc I never planned on jumping in a tub of ice, but he gave me a good phrase to live by: "don't be a p*ssy" (noted)

The location was amazing, food was served, and I met some great people, one of which was @michaeljames_presents and bro is super grounded for everything that he's a part of fr. Spent the whole day joking about how "you don't see this type of stuff in the hood" lol

@therichladyamerika and @khadirah1 were super cool on the whole thing as well, kept everyone positive, even though we were about to jump into 37 degree waters! 

All in all I have to say, I did it! I took the plunge without dipping a toe, jumping in full blast and came out realizing life is about just taking the plunge 

#actor #actorlife #gig #giglife #bg #set #location #coldplunge #background #influencer #xyz #icebath

Just like your typical workplace, there are good days, bad days, and just....days lol And although this was a 2 day shoot, it was just ....a day.

Lined up for COVID testing, grabbed our masks, and boarded the buses to head to location and to holding. Now, holding is never luxurious to my knowledge, but this one I would consider a "sheep herd." 3-4 buses worth of humans under the tent in the video above (sometimes for hours until they need you), so space can sometimes be very limited and good luck finding a spot to charge your phone lol

Nonetheless, set itself was a great experience, had some A/C issues in the building but hey, it's work lol

This time didn't meet anyone spectacular, no big celebs popped in, no wild lessons to teach, just a typical day in the office. So, if there's anyone reading these and going to take the jump based off of my posts, I'm letting you know right HERE, every day is NOT exciting, but worth it regardless to be working

This one was possibly the best set that I've been on tbh! Full of action from day 1, celebs in and out I couldn't even catch them all, close ups and features, couldn't ask for too much more as bg.

I applied for this role to be a specialty background extra as a trombone player in a band, had NOO idea I was going to get the spot but I'm glad I did.  Not only did I run into a grip of people that I've seen on other sets, but I met some phenominal people! 

Wardrobe was LIKE THAT! Can't even lie, my head was NOT looking the best that morning, but they got me suited up and sent over to the hair folk, between that woman braiding down the dreads and brotha man hitting me with that holy taper, I felt like SOMEBODY before 8am lol

*which is another thing to not worry about, if they want you to look a certain way, there are people for that. Not on EVERY set, but... most of them*

I met up with the other band members and man, when I say you woulda thought we were a REAL band by noon, I mean it! @rj_music9
on trumpet, @shana.b.music
on bass, @travk_cmm on the sticks, and big @thezeslimkornegay on piano. Chopping it up, cracking jokes, sneaking off when it's nothing to do, we made a REAL band lol 

I was able to meet @yolandaadams gaze, see @lodivadevine in action and I was hoping to get over to @officialmichaeljai for a picture but I didn't make it in time, but seeing him in person was still a gift. 

This happened to be the season finale that we were shooting so it ended in a real celebration, until Ze decided to "take us to church" on the piano and pxssed off the director lmao But maaaaaan, if I could do those two days over again, I swear I would

This was the last show that I did before the WGA Strike began. As soon as I pulled up, one of the crew members walked up and asked if they could use my car for a scene (sure, why not? lol) We were off to a good start!

I was told that I had been putting in a lot of work, this was one of the times I realized it. Before I knew it, I felt like a regular on set. I was able to help people with their paperwok effortlessly, I was listing all of the different set lingo to newcomers so they wouldn't be lost, in a few months time, I went from being completely oblivious to "seasoned." lol

Very first person I ran into on this set was a fresh actor, but super talented musician named @playy2day who ended up getting a featured role in the scene (him and like 8 other people out of nowhere, that director made half the BG SAG-eligible in one day!) 

Around lunch, all my fellow BG was letting me know how good the acting that I was doing was. "bro....you really looked HURT over there, I was like I need to step my faces up haha" Even though we were all laughing at it, it made me feel good that my performance was that believable. 

I got dirty, I got my shirt ripped up, I "died" I helped people learn. I got to see @itsreginaecarter (leader of the group) and it was overall a really good time. Can't wait to see what the next set I will be on will bring

#actor #acting #set #setlife #bg #background #wardrobe #crafty #crew #cast #gig #film #series #movie #wga

I'm not SAG (yet) so I don't know all of the ins-and-outs of it but here's what I've seen. I started doing this actor thing heavy in February, and I've been on my share of sets at this point. I've been arond extras, cast, and crew, I SEE what all goes into production, the hours alone is crazy. 

I was being booked consistently, multiple gigs per week, then suddenly, EVERYTHING slowed down around April, then....nothing. It felt almost like another COVID fr looking for work but nothing (paid) coming around. Not long after, I see the WGA is going on strike, and gigs got lower and lower, some casting agencies haven't posted a gig at all since May! But to see how the #SAG actors are being shafted is crazy af. I mean, if I'm not mistaken, it costs them like $1600/yr. just to be a PART of it, how tf do you sent someone a check for change when they're a part of one of the biggest streaming shows ever? 

A lot of us are struggling right now, and in a mulit-billion dollar industry, how hard would it really be to give payment where payment is due to the people that literally put in the blood, sweat, tears, practice, experience, soul, and personality to the very thing that brought you your billions? Just know, if this SAG strike happens on top of the WGA strike, get ready for a stale production year, break your dvds back out....

#WGA #WGAStrike #SAGAFTRA #actorslife
